entry.title: Add feature flag to enable media compression
entry.content:
From Gen-12 onwards on Intel, minigbm can allocate compressed buffers

and the functionality landed in CL:4655427. In order to safely guard

the feature and have all the support for compressed buffers in place for chrome, this CL adds a feature flag to enable Media compression on Intel. This flag, when enabled, sets the environmental variable to allow minigbm to allocate media compressed buffers that are suitable for use in the hardware video codec pipeline. This CL also adds strong assertions at important places where |gbm_create_device()| is called to ensure the minigbm environment variable is set before potentially

initializing minigbm.



This CL is a follow-up cleanup to CL:4629410 to ensure the environment

variable is set up in test environments.



BUG=b:271455200

TEST=deploy to chrome and check if flag is enabled

entry.title: Revert "[Files app] Make `GuestOsSharePath` depend on `VolumeManager`"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 4a3c90aceee14e4502da1b529398e16977e35cc2.



Reason for revert: https://crbug.com/1491372, CrostiniSshfsHelperTest failing



Original change's description:

> [Files app] Make `GuestOsSharePath` depend on `VolumeManager`

>

> The `GuestOsSharePath` currently registers as an observer of

> `VolumeManager` in it's constructor and de-registers in its Shutdown

> method. It's possible that `VolumeManager` is destructed before

> `GuestOsSharePath` and in the Shutdown method it then tries to create a

> `VolumeManager` instance.

>

> This adds the DependsOn explicitly in the `GuestOsSharePathFactory` and

> adds a new method to just find the existing `VolumeManager` instead of

> trying to create a new one. The former is probably not strictly

> necessary given the DependsOn, but can't hurt to ensure a new one isn't

> created.

>

> Furthermore this ensures the observer is removed from the `DriveFsHost`

> and updates to use `base::ScopedObservation` instead. Given the

> dependency on `DriveFsHost` this also ensures a `DependsOn` is added

> for `drive::DriveIntegrationService` as well.

>

entry.title: [DownloadBubble] Remove last download time pref
entry.content:
This removes the last download time pref and updates code relying on it

to use the time supplied by DownloadBubbleUpdateService::GetDisplayInfo

instead. This updates the algorithm for calculating the last downloaded

time in the display info, by recording the time when a download is

updated and becomes no longer in-progress. We assume that when a

download is updated to a not-in-progress state, no further updates will

be sent aside from cancellation. In particular, this takes the time when

a download is marked insecure or dangerous (as they are considered not

in-progress).



This is done because:

1. The original reason for persisting the last downloaded time between

browser sessions is no longer relevant, because the download toolbar

button is no longer shown upon browser startup for performance

reasons. (The pref was added in crrev.com/c/3472822.)

2. Reading the pref on every single update may be expensive and doesn't

make a difference most of the time.



The resulting behavior change is that, in the case where a download

finished less than an hour ago in a previous Chrome session and the user

downloads another file (causing the toolbar button to be shown), we will

no longer schedule the toolbar button disappearance for 1 hr after the

original download, but will instead schedule it for 1 hr after the last

download finished *in the current browser session*.

entry.title: [ios] Fix SerializeWebStateList to keep items with pending navigations
entry.content:
SerializeWebStateList had a bug where the items with pending items but

no navigation items. It had no visible impact because the session will

be saved again when the item navigation commits.



However, with the new session serialization logic, the WebStateList

state is not considered dirty if the only change is a navigation that

commit. This could results in data loss because in that case the list

will not reference this item.



Fix GetIndexOfWebStatesToDrop() to consider that WebState with a load

pending are not dropped (they may still be dropped on load if the app

could not save the session after the navigation commit, e.g. in case

of a crash).



Update the unit test to check that those tabs are not dropped.

entry.title: Sync: Simplify ProtocolTypes() and EncryptableUserTypes()
entry.content:
The concept of "protocol types" existed to distinguish from "proxy

types", which didn't have a protocol representation.

As of crrev.com/c/4922312, the concept of proxy types doesn't exist

anymore, so "protocol types" is now the same as "all types", so no more

need to explicitly list all the types.



There's one minor behavior difference: Previously, ProtocolTypes()

didn't include ModelType::SEGMENTATION, which was an oversight. (This

ModelType is partially implemented, but not actually used yet.)



Additionally and similarly, this CL also slightly simplifies

EncryptableUserTypes(): Now there's no more need to drop

non-protocol types, because they don't exist.
